Emap Plc is seeking to sell its
trade-magazine business, valued at about 100 million pounds
($158 million), the  Independent on Sunday  reported, citing
people it didnâ€™t identify.  The company has talked to Collins Stewart Hawkpoint Plc
about advising on the sale, which is likely to take place this
year, according to the newspaper. The unit, Emap Inform,
publishes titles such as Broadcast, Retail Week and Nursing
Times. Emap is owned by Apax Partners LLP and Guardian Media
